                <note type="abstract">Represents an abridged version of chap. two of the author’s MA thesis <ref target="https://biblia-arabica.com/bibl/ZWYUS5U6">https://biblia-arabica.com/bibl/ZWYUS5U6</ref>. Includes an edition of four Geniza fragments of reworked versions of Saadiah Gaon’s Judaeo-Arabic translation of the Pentateuch in Arabic script (Gen 4:24; Exod 21:8–19; Num 8:1–4; 13:1–4; 16:1–4; 29:3–29; 30:1–8, 14–31:14) and Proverbs (23:5–24:6). Based on the characteristics of the reworkings (e.g., a tendency toward strict literalism, preference for the Qaraite translational lexicon, inclusion of alternate translations, the use of Arabic script) Vollandt concludes that the fragments were produced by and for Qaraite scholars/scribes associated with the Palestinian circle of the 10th–11th centuries.</note>
